page.title: 03Housing
page.content: The larger settlement can be found at {Stanford Dingley}where the{River Pang is bridged. The only other concentrated collection of houses can be found in{Tutt's Clump,}where there are some comparitively small housing estates. The majority of houses can be found on or just off the minor roads approaching these two central focal points. The majority being semi-detached or detached. While the majority of the houses along routeways appear to have been built in the past seventy years, the majority of Stanford Dingley's housing is much older and possesses large gardens. Some of the original constructions may date back to the{Georgian}eras and the two public houses represent fine examples of{Jacobean}architecture.
